- Detector resolution: The energy resolutions of
measured neutron spectra are at maximum about 20%
for about 2000 MeV neutrons of highest energy at 0
degree and 7.5 degree, about 20% for about 1000 MeV
neutrons of highest energy at 15 degree and 30
degree, and about 40% for about 600 MeV neutrons of
highest energy at 60 degree and 90 degree, which
were produced by 800 MeV/nucleon Si ions.
